# FQL-GUI-Launcher Monorepo Boundary Rules

## Scope decision first
Before writing or editing code, always determine:
1. which package is the target,
2. whether the task belongs to the design system or a business project,
3. whether any part should be promoted into the design system.

## Package boundaries
- `ai-agent-design-system` is the design system source of truth.
- `projects/*` are business consumer projects.
- Do not implement real business flows inside `ai-agent-design-system/app/*`.
- `ai-agent-design-system/app/*` is only for demo, playground, docs, preview, and verification pages.
- Shared primitives belong in `ai-agent-design-system/components/ui/*`.
- Shared semantic wrappers belong in `ai-agent-design-system/components/fql/*`.
- Theme token mapping belongs in `ai-agent-design-system/app/globals.css`.
- Registry files and registry build flow belong in `ai-agent-design-system`.

## Reuse rules
- If a UI pattern is reusable across multiple projects, propose or implement it in the design system first.
- Business projects should consume existing design-system components before creating local duplicates.
- Do not recreate `components/ui/*` primitives inside `projects/*` unless explicitly approved as an experiment.
- Do not hardcode design tokens in business projects when semantic tokens already exist upstream.

## Agent behavior
- Start multi-file work with a short plan.
- State target package before implementation.
- List changed files after implementation.
- If code created in `projects/*` looks reusable, explicitly flag it as a promotion candidate for the design system.

## Reading order
When entering a package, read in this order:
1. monorepo root `AGENTS.md`
2. package-level `AGENTS.md`
3. package-level `.cursor/rules/*`
4. relevant theme, component, registry, and page files
